@minux i experience some troubles moving from python to golang as i use integer keys a lot. The python behavior: 

    >>> d = {1: 1, 5: 4}
    >>> json.dumps(d)
    '{"1": 1, "5": 4}'
    >>> d = {1.4: 1, 5.1: 4}
    >>> d
    {1.4: 1, 5.1: 4}
    >>> json.dumps(d)
    '{"1.4": 1, "5.1": 4}'

Maybe we can introduce a special method inside json module for marshalling such data?
